channel.title: Missing include files (ssi2, squig, si, ss, osi, uss, library+)? clicky here!
channel.description:
Is there something wrong with your script? Something as an Include file? Then [B]GET A NEW SCRIPT[/B], since they must be [i]out-dated[/i] then. Best place to look for much more [i]better and advanced[/i] scripts is the [url=http://SRL-Forums.com/forum/]SRL-Forums[/url], however, you must be registered there for 7 days and have posted 10 [u]useful[/u] posts ;) So don't go spamming!
Most of the scripts around here are [B]OUT-DATED[/B], so don't bother posting if the first posts date (inc. Edit date) is more than [b][u]ONE MONTH[/u][/b] old!
The best include to get is [url=http://srl-forums.com]SRL[/url]! Since it is one of the [i]ONLY[/i] include updated for the [I]NEW[/I] RuneScape. The other include that is updated is [url=http://phoenixprogramming.org/Downloads/scarincludes.html]Planet Hell[/url], which can be downloaded from [url=http://phoenixprogramming.org/Downloads/scarincludes.html]here[/url] or directly from SCAR (File> Download Includes).
